s=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 21, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fyf1665702757387.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fyf1665702757387.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fyf1665702757387.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fyf1665702757387\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__float_304535\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface data type that holds a number with a floating decimal point.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__topic_d92510e1_d92511e1_d92512e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92513e1_d92514e1_d92515e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">float</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ParameterName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Direction</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92516e1_d92517e1_d92518e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">float</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">VariableName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__topic_d61572e1_d61573e1_d61574e1_d61575e1_d61576e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d891368e83\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__d5970e20\">Use in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">params</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">variables</span> blocks to define the data type of a parameter or variable. The data type can be selected when defining fields, global variables, and component variables.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__topic_d61577e1_d61578e1_d61579e1_d61580e1_d61581e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d891368e98\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92528e1_d92529e1_d92530e1\">Uniface internally supports a platform-independent precision of 38 digits for the mantissa, plus one for rounding, and four digits for the exponent, as follows:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92531e1_d92532e1_d92533e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">+/-\n               (99,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999e+/- 9999)</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92534e1_d92535e1_d92536e1\">When storing data, it depends on the DBMS whether this high precision is supported.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92537e1_d92538e1_d92539e1\">Fields defined as data type <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">float</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">numeric</span> can accept a scientific notation. For example, you could enter <code class=\"ph codeph\">1.23e-5</code> in a field with data type <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">float</span> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">123e-5</code> in a field with data type <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">numeric</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fyf1665702757387__p_d92540e1_d92541e1_d92542e1\">If no display format is specified for a field with data type float, the field syntax length is used when formatting the value.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fnk1665702757456.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Extracting Values From Numeric Data</a><p>When you are working with data stored as a Numeric or Float value, you can extract information such as the integer part or the fractional part of a value. This extraction is done with a numeric extraction parameter.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gpd1665702757526.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes for Numeric Data</a><p>The Uniface Numeric and Float data types are associated with many packing codes.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/alk1665702757606.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Floating Point Packing Codes (F)</a><p>When high precision is required, use the F packing code, which stores numbers as an exponent (2 n) and a mantissa (the number by which to multiply the exponent).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527737\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527737\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "float Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 21, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface data type that holds a number with a floating decimal point. float ParameterName : Direction float VariableName Use Use in params and variables blocks to define the data type of a parameter or variable. The data type can be selected when defining fields, global variables, and component variables. Description Uniface internally supports a platform-independent precision of 38 digits for the mantissa, plus one for rounding, and four digits for the exponent, as follows: +/- (99,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999,999e+/- 9999) When storing data, it depends on the DBMS whether this high precision is supported. Fields defined as data type float or numeric can accept a scientific notation. For example, you could enter 1.23e-5 in a field with data type float and 123e-5 in a field with data type numeric . If no display format is specified for a field with data type float, the field syntax length is used when formatting the value. Related Links Extracting Values From Numeric Data When you are working with data stored as a Numeric or Float value, you can extract information such as the integer part or the fractional part of a value. This extraction is done with a numeric extraction parameter. Packing Codes for Numeric Data The Uniface Numeric and Float data types are associated with many packing codes. Floating Point Packing Codes (F) When high precision is required, use the F packing code, which stores numbers as an exponent (2 n) and a mantissa (the number by which to multiply the exponent). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}